	<doc for="DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs"/> class.</para>
		</summary>
		<param name="commandSource">The source of the command.</param>
		<param name=" newPageIndex">The index of the page selected by the user from the page selection element of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</param>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use this constructor to create and initialize a new
      instance of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs"/>class.</para>
			<para>When an instance of <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridCommandEventArgs"/> is created by a
   call to this constructor, the following properties are initialized to the
   specified values.</para>
			<list type="table">
				<listheader>
					<term>Properties</term>
					<description>Initial Value</description>
				</listheader>
				<item>
					<term> CommandSource</term>
					<description>The
      <paramref name="commandSource"/> parameter.</description>
				</item>
				<item>
					<term> NewPageIndex</term>
					<description>The
      <paramref name="newPageIndex"/> parameter.</description>
				</item>
			</list>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to create and
      initialize a new instance of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs"/> class. </para>
			<codelink SampleID="Classic DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs Example" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
	</doc>
	<doc for="DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.CommandSource">
		<summary>
			<para> Gets the source of the command.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para>The source of the command.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.CommandSource"/> property to determine the source of the command that raised the event. Because this event is
   only raised when a button in the page selection element of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control
   is clicked, the returned source is a
<see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridItem"/> 
that represents the
page selection element. </para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.CommandSource"/> property
   to programmatically control the command source that raises the
   event. </para>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridAllowPaging" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.PageIndexChanged"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.OnPageIndexChanged"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.NewPageIndex">
		<summary>
			<para>Gets the index of the page selected by the user in the page
      selection element of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</para>
		</summary>
		<value>
			<para> The index of the page selected by the user in the page
      selection element of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.</para>
		</value>
		<remarks>
			<para>Use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.NewPageIndex"/> property
   to determine the index of
   the page selected by the user in the page selection element of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.
   This value is often used to set the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.CurrentPageIndex"/> property of
   the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control to display the selected
   page.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to use the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.NewPageIndex"/> property
   to determine the index of the page selected by the user in the page selection element of the
<see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control. This value is then used to 
   set the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.CurrentPageIndex"/> property of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control to display the selected page. </para>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridAllowPaging" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.PageIndexChanged"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.OnPageIndexChanged"/>
	</doc>
	<doc for="DataGridPageChangedEventArgs">
		<summary>
			<para>Provides data for the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.PageIndexChanged"/> event of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control.
   This class cannot be
   inherited.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para> The <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.PageIndexChanged"/> event is raised when a
   button in the page selection
   element of the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/> control is clicked.</para>
			<para>For a list of initial property values for an instance of
<see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs"/>, see the <see cref="M:System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventArgs.#ctor"/> constructor.</para>
			<para>For more information about handling events, see <see topic="cpconEventsOverview"/>.</para>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example demonstrates how to specify and
      code a handler for the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.PageIndexChanged"/> event. It
      displays pages on the <see cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
      control in 10-item increments.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="DataGridAllowPaging" SnippetID="1"/>
			<codelink SampleID="PageIndexChanged" SnippetID="1"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGridPageChangedEventHandler"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.PageIndexChanged"/>
		<seealso cref="System.Web.UI.WebControls.DataGrid.OnPageIndexChanged"/>
	</doc>
